This paper is about optimizing the parameters of deep neural networks using a genetic algorithm aided by a bi-generative adversarial network. The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of different deep neural network architectures, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.GR (Graphics).
